body:
Hi everybody,

I'm sorry that this is at the moment more of a quick log dump than a beautifully crafted bug report.
Hopefully I'll find the time to split it up into several different problems
within the next few weeks.

So, the issue seems quite simple from outside-when ratox is called by
another client that then hangs up before the call could be answered,
ratox crashes.

When observing the situation under valgrind, ratox does not crash,
but it seems like the invalid memory reads are done solely inside toxcore.
I don't want to blame anybody (you guys are great), but this seems like
a toxcore issue.

Also, before crashing, toxcore logs the following line:

    /build/toxcore/src/c-toxcore-0.1.8/toxav/msi.c:786 [handle_pop](2): Friend canceled call invite

For the first problem (the conditional jump based on an uninitialized value), this seems to be
a result of a malfunction of [unpack_nodes()](https://github.com/TokTok/c-toxcore/blob/master/toxcore/DHT.c#L486) returning a number of nodes different from the number of nodes actually processed for a certain packet. I'll try to get the data for that specific packet.

@iphydf @irungentoo This one seems pretty serious. Needs to be fixed ASAP.
@pranomostro Can you provide more details about the issues? Would you mean submitting a patch for fixing these? Did you investigated more?
I fixed some uninitialised data things recently. Can you reproduce this issue?
Okay, the bug in toxcore is fixed, now I have to fix one in ratox. Thanks a lot!
